The paper proposes a deep learning technique for the classification of healthy and glaucomatous eyes using raw, unsegmented OCT volumes. This involves the use of a 3D Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) and the computation of Class Activation Maps (CAM) to identify regions of the OCT volume that are important for glaucoma detection. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it involves the analysis of medical images using deep learning techniques. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category, as it compares the accuracy of the proposed deep learning approach with various feature-based machine learning algorithms. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) for glaucoma detection. Finally, the paper may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, as it involves the identification of important regions in the OCT volume using Class Activation Maps.
